    "role_lines": [
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "What had he done, to make him fly the land?",
            {
                "preceding_direction_line": "1"
            }
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "You must have patience, madam."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "He had none:"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "His flight was madness: when our actions do not,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Our fears do make us traitors."
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "You know not"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "Whether it was his wisdom or his fear."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Wisdom! to leave his wife, to leave his babes,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "His mansion and his titles in a place"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "From whence himself does fly? He loves us not;"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "He wants the natural touch: for the poor wren,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "The most diminutive of birds, will fight,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Her young ones in her nest, against the owl."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "All is the fear and nothing is the love;"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "As little is the wisdom, where the flight"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "So runs against all reason."
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "My dearest coz,"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "I pray you, school yourself: but for your husband,"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "He is noble, wise, judicious, and best knows"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "The fits o' the season. I dare not speak"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "much further;"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "But cruel are the times, when we are traitors"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "And do not know ourselves, when we hold rumour"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "From what we fear, yet know not what we fear,"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "But float upon a wild and violent sea"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "Each way and move. I take my leave of you:"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "Shall not be long but I'll be here again:"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "Things at the worst will cease, or else climb upward"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "To what they were before. My pretty cousin,"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "Blessing upon you!"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Father'd he is, and yet he's fatherless."
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "I am so much a fool, should I stay longer,"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "It would be my disgrace and your discomfort:"
        ],
        [
            "ROSS",
            "I take my leave at once.",
            {
                "following_direction_line": "2"
            }
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Sirrah, your father's dead;",
            {
                "preceding_direction_line": "2"
            }
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "And what will you do now? How will you live?"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "As birds do, mother."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "What, with worms and flies?"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "With what I get, I mean; and so do they."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Poor bird! thou'ldst never fear the net nor lime,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "The pitfall nor the gin."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Why should I, mother? Poor birds they are not set for."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "My father is not dead, for all your saying."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Yes, he is dead; how wilt thou do for a father?"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Nay, how will you do for a husband?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Why, I can buy me twenty at any market."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Then you'll buy 'em to sell again."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Thou speak'st with all thy wit: and yet, i' faith,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "With wit enough for thee."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Was my father a traitor, mother?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Ay, that he was."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "What is a traitor?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Why, one that swears and lies."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "And be all traitors that do so?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Every one that does so is a traitor, and must be hanged."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "And must they all be hanged that swear and lie?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Every one."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Who must hang them?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Why, the honest men."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Then the liars and swearers are fools,"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "for there are liars and swearers enow to beat"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "the honest men and hang up them."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Now, God help thee, poor monkey!"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "But how wilt thou do for a father?"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "If he were dead, you'ld weep for"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "him: if you would not, it were a good sign"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "that I should quickly have a new father."
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Poor prattler, how thou talk'st!",
            {
                "following_direction_line": "3"
            }
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "Bless you, fair dame! I am not to you known,",
            {
                "preceding_direction_line": "3"
            }
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "Though in your state of honour I am perfect."
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "I doubt some danger does approach you nearly:"
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "If you will take a homely man's advice,"
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "Be not found here; hence, with your little ones."
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "To fright you thus, methinks, I am too savage;"
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "To do worse to you were fell cruelty,"
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "Which is too nigh your person. Heaven preserve you!"
        ],
        [
            "Messenger",
            "I dare abide no longer.",
            {
                "following_direction_line": "4"
            }
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Whither should I fly?",
            {
                "preceding_direction_line": "4"
            }
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "I have done no harm. But I remember now"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "I am in this earthly world; where to do harm"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Is often laudable, to do good sometime"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Accounted dangerous folly: why then, alas,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Do I put up that womanly defence,"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "To say I have done no harm?",
            {
                "following_direction_line": "5"
            }
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "What are these faces?",
            {
                "preceding_direction_line": "5"
            }
        ],
        [
            "First Murderer",
            "Where is your husband?"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "I hope, in no place so unsanctified"
        ],
        [
            "LADY MACDUFF",
            "Where such as thou mayst find him."
        ],
        [
            "First Murderer",
            "He's a traitor."
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Thou liest, thou shag-hair'd villain!"
        ],
        [
            "First Murderer",
            "What, you egg!",
            {
                "following_direction_line": "6"
            }
        ],
        [
            "First Murderer",
            "Young fry of treachery!",
            {
                "preceding_direction_line": "6"
            }
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "He has kill'd me, mother:"
        ],
        [
            "Son",
            "Run away, I pray you!",
            {
                "following_direction_line": "7"
            }
        ]
